arch any artifact or dependencies essential for normal use. It seems like I might conclude that no extra deterministic setup is required unless new information suggests otherwise. It looks like choosing no_action is safe unless evidence for additional setup appears, but I must note risks of using deprecated wrappers or optional APIs that might affect tests. I need to ensure everything is in a single JSON format.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Summarizing dependencies and setup**\\n\\nI could summarize that there’s no extra dependency, Docker, or environment needed because the artifact is just a legacy wrapper around Eclipse Sisu and Guice. It resolves transitive core dependencies, allowing meaningful test coverage through various functionalities like Guice bean scanning in regular JUnit tests. \\n\\nThere’s agent guidance about not needing environment variables or system properties. If I’m updating tests for version 2.4.1, I should switch to using `org.eclipse.sisu.space.QualifiedTypeBinder.hear(Class, Object)` instead of the older call, which could help with any javac compile issues.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra setup is needed: sisu-inject-bean 2.4.1 resolves its core Guice, CDI, and Eclipse Sisu dependencies transitively, and meaningful coverage is reachable with ordinary generated JUnit tests exercising bean scanning, URLClassSpace, SisuGuice, and binder behavior.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment variables or system properties are required. If adapting the existing 2.4.0 tests for 2.4.1, update calls to org.eclipse.sisu.space.QualifiedTypeBinder.hear to the current two-argument signature hear(Class, Object) rather than the older three-argument form.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The artifact is a deprecated legacy wrapper over Eclipse Sisu APIs, so generated tests should prefer public wrapper APIs and current method signatures.\",\n    \"The POM declares optional SLF4J, OSGi, JUnit, and TestNG integrations; do not add those dependencies unless tests deliberately target those optional integration paths.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_029f01d4bd94ba8e016a3e5727ab848193beb1240fcd4a7399\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1650, "output": 751, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31585, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782470429447, "responseId": "resp_029f01d4bd94ba8e016a3e571df754819389f14fa898a62362"}}
